<br />
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The strategy is the same that in Splendor of Gondor v1.0, but i put pathfinder in order to play my sites whenever i want and when i need to.<br />
(useful if there is no prancing poney to begin with). I also put the common Merry instead the rare one because he is a lot more agressive in his common way.<br />
<br />
here is the old strategy:<br />
Strategy <br />
In the fellowship phase with cardds like no stranger to the shadows or an able guide, your opponent will have trouble trying to play any big minion he has. <br />
Stealth and intuition to protect the hibbits, and some swords too. <br />
Go fast with those preety ranger sites through the game. <br />
a lot of healing stuff in the case you get some wounds. <br />
<br />
in the shadow phase my favorite thing is to use my uruk spy along with the cruel caradhras (or the worry too) to add a bunch of burdens, thats a nice combo i figured out the other day. <br />
If you cannot afford that combo you can attack with all the archers in the shadow part or with luck play lurtz and kick some major azz here. <br />
